Police seized guns and ammunition from a number of homes in Pietermaritzburg on Monday night. The raids were part of an operation being run by a specialist team from a base at the Plessislaer police station. Colonel Thembeka Mbele, spokesperson for the KZN SAPS, said officers raided a house in Mpumuza where a 47-year-old man was found in possession of three illegal firearms: a rifle, shotgun and pistol. “A further two licensed firearms, which consists of a shotgun and a revolver, were seized by police for further investigation,” she added. Police also seized 100 rounds of ammunition from the man, who appeared at the Pietermaritzburg Magistrates Court on Tuesday. He has been charged with the unlawful possession of firearms and ammunition.